{
  "text": "[21] Soil temperatures are slightly warmer in CLM3.5 (CONTROL) compared to CLM3 (CONTROL CLM3 ), as noted in section 2.3, which results in an even lower diagnosed area containing near-surface permafrost (8.5 \u00c2 10 6 km 2 ). When compared to observed estimates for the area of continuous permafrost (90 -100% coverage) and discontinuous permafrost (50 -90% coverage) combined (11.2-13.5 \u00c2 10 6 km 2 for the equivalent region poleward of 45\u00b0N [CITATION_1] ), the total area simulated in CONTROL is clearly biased low. In the organic soil and deeper soil column experiments, the area with near-surface permafrost increases to 10.5 and 10.7 \u00c2 10 6 km 2 , respectively. These values compare reasonably with the observed permafrost extent, especially when one considers that the off-line experiments appear to be biased low by $0.5 \u00c2 10 6 km 2 compared to the coupled simulation. It is worth noting here that each grid box is represented by a single soil column. This prevents the explicit simulation of the sporadic or isolated permafrost classes which are typically found at the southern margins of the discontinuous permafrost boundary.",
